headline: Polymarket Lists War-Related Contracts as Regulators and Lawmakers Push Back

headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Buying Intercontinental Exchange (ICE) After Strong Multi‑Year Gains?
summary: If you are wondering whether Intercontinental Exchange at around US$166 per share is offering fair value or a stretched price, this breakdown is designed to help you make sense of what you are paying for. The stock has recorded returns of 0.4% over the past week, 2.1% over the past month, 4.2% year to date, 16.1% over the past year, 61.3% over three years, and 54.7% over five years.
